C PROJECT SONG\";s:11:\"author_name\";s:3:\"NPR\";s:10:\"author_url\";s:43:\"https://www.youtube.com/nationalpublicradio\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"video\";s:6:\"height\";i:405;s:5:\"width\";i:720;s:7:\"version\";s:3:\"1.0\";s:13:\"provider_name\";s:7:\"YouTube\";s:12:\"provider_url\";s:24:\"https://www.youtube.com/\";s:16:\"thumbnail_height\";i:360;s:15:\"thumbnail_width\";i:480;s:13:\"thumbnail_url\";s:48:\"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/jiM6XIoW6ZY/hqdefault.jpg\";s:4:\"html\";s:234:\"<iframe width=\"720\" height=\"405\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/jiM6XIoW6ZY?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\";}'),(5,142,'_oembed_d05e76528988186233906debc14186bc','<iframe title=\"Moby &#039;The Day&#039; Official video featuring Heather Graham\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/22694972?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963\" width=\"720\" height=\"405\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>'),(6,142,'_oembed_response_d05e76528988186233906debc14186bc','O:8:\"stdClass\":21:{s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"video\";s:7:\"version\";s:3:\"1.0\";s:13:\"provider_name\";s:5:\"Vimeo\";s:12:\"provider_url\";s:18:\"https://vimeo.com/\";s:5:\"title\";s:54:\"Moby \'The Day\' Official video featuring Heather Graham\";s:11:\"author_name\";s:4:\"Moby\";s:10:\"author_url\";s:22:\"https://vimeo.com/moby\";s:7:\"is_plus\";s:1:\"0\";s:12:\"account_type\";s:5:\"basic\";s:4:\"html\";s:274:\"<iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/22694972?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963\" width=\"720\" height=\"405\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen title=\"Moby &amp;#039;The Day&amp;#039; Official video featuring Heather Graham\"></iframe>\";s:5:\"width\";i:720;s:6:\"height\";i:405;s:8:\"duration\";i:202;s:11:\"description\";s:1780:\"Official video for the first single to be taken from Moby\'s forthcoming album (and photo book) \'Destroyed\'. The video features Heather Graham alongside Moby and was directed by Evan Bernard and eyeball.\n\nMore info on \'The Day\' and \'Destroyed\' here: http://moby.com\n\nVideo Director: Evan Bernard and eyeball: http://www.eyeballnyc.com\nVideo Producer: Kerri Kleiner\nProduction Company: Hello And Company\n\nIndirectly inspired by David Bowie and Brian Enos production circa Low and Heroes (which moby believes is now part of his DNA), the song is one of the few tracks from Destroyed that moby himself sang on. The Day was written in a hotel room in Spain at dawn when I hadnt slept, recounts moby. I wrote it on an acoustic guitar and recorded it on my phone, brought it home and re-recorded it with the old broken-down electronics I have in my studio.\n\nA deeply personal song about late night desperation and dark-night-of-the-soul disquietude, the video for The Day (directed by Evan Bernard) features Mobys friend and actress Heather Graham in the role of a nurse/guardian angel who gets to slaughter demons,\" explains moby. \"I had this simple idea of Heather as an angel in a hospital. Evan expanded upon it and made it a lot more interesting, a lot more compelling. \n\nThe basic plot of the video, according to Heather, is \"a woman is lying in a hospital bed and I am the nurse and I give her some oxygen. Then it cuts to me as the angel flying, and then you see this scary demon. The director elaborates: \"She (the angel) is the defender of righteousness. She represents good, and she\'s defeating evil. Climaxing in a metaphysical battle between demon and angel, the video is filled with surreal imagery in an eerie clinical setting.\";s:13:\"thumbnail_url\";s:42:\"https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/146945252_640\";s:15:\"thumbnail_width\";i:640;s:16:\"thumbnail_height\";i:360;s:30:\"thumbnail_url_with_play_button\";s:160:\"https://i.vimeocdn.com/filter/overlay?src0=https%3A%2F%2Fi.vimeocdn.com%2Fvideo%2F146945252_640&src1=http%3A%2F%2Ff.vimeocdn.com%2Fp%2F